{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17492574","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17492574"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T06:36:32+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T06:36:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1103"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1103","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1103"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.22,0.32,0.34,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1103"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109030"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1103","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1103"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2019-11-15T21:20:56+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-16T12:00:52+09:30","updatedAction":"commented","acceptedAt":"2022-10-03T15:42:02+10:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-25 21:06:49"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1103"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91396"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"251"},{"type":"tags","id":"459"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"1151"},{"type":"tags","id":"1393"},{"type":"tags","id":"4046"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5795"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7153"},{"type":"contributions","id":"12792"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40698"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91396"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109030","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/109030"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 81-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-month history of poor appetite and occasional nausea. He has lost 4 kg of weight over this period. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. He is a retired builder and has never smoked.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Abdominal examination reveals mild epigastric tenderness. An endoscopic examination is arranged (Image 1). A comparative view from a normal stomach is shown (Image 2).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn this case the diagnosis should be apparent from the patient\u0027s history and endoscopic findings. There are a number of different ways in which this condition can present.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"In general, which one of the following is the most likely initial presenting symptom?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Vomiting of undigested food","Tiredness and fatigue","Haematemesis","Anorexia and nausea","Back pain"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe endoscopic images show a large ulcer on the lesser curve of the stomach with a necrotic base and raised, rolled edges, which are characteristic features of gastric cancer. Understanding the typical progression of symptoms is crucial for early detection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnorexia and nausea\u003C/strong\u003E are typically the earliest presenting symptoms of gastric cancer, often occurring before other more concerning symptoms develop. These symptoms, along with weight loss, form the characteristic presenting triad of gastric cancer.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVomiting of undigested food\u003C/strong\u003E typically occurs in more advanced disease when the tumour causes mechanical obstruction of the gastric outlet. This is a late presenting feature indicating advanced disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETiredness and fatigue\u003C/strong\u003E are non-specific symptoms that may occur in gastric cancer, usually due to chronic blood loss leading to iron deficiency anaemia, but these are not typically initial presenting symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHaematemesis\u003C/strong\u003E is an uncommon presenting feature of gastric cancer. While gastric tumours may bleed, they more commonly present with melaena rather than frank haematemesis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBack pain\u003C/strong\u003E may occur in advanced disease with posterior invasion or metastatic spread but is not a typical initial presenting symptom of gastric cancer.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Gastric cancer classically appears as an ulcer with a necrotic base and raised rolled edges on endoscopy","Anorexia and nausea are among the earliest presenting symptoms of gastric cancer","Late symptoms of gastric cancer include vomiting and weight loss, indicating more advanced disease"],"references":["Smyth EC, Nilsson M, Grabsch HI, et al. Gastric cancer. Lancet 2020, 396:635-48. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32861308/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91396"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1103"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"18315"},{"type":"media","id":"18316"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"18315","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/18315"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/93fe373a-a4b1-4ed0-94d8-f7c33fec21e5.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/93fe373a-a4b1-4ed0-94d8-f7c33fec21e5.jpg","isPr